-- Doan’s Goal Gives Coyotes 1-0 Win Over Predators in NHL Playoffs
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-05-05T04:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-05/doan-s-goal-gives-coyotes-1-0-win-over-predators-in-nhl-playoffs.html
Shane Doan fired a 10-foot backhand
shot into the net to give the Phoenix Coyotes a 1-0 victory over
the  Nashville Predators  in the second round of the National
Hockey League’s Stanley Cup playoffs.  Doan’s goal came 14 minutes, 25 seconds into the first
period at Bridgestone Arena in Nashville. The Coyotes with a 3-1
lead in the best-of-seven semifinal series are within one game
of advancing to the Western Conference finals.  Mike Smith  had 25 saves for the Coyotes, while Pekka Rinne
stopped 23 shots for the Predators.  The Coyotes move back to their home ice to host the
Predators for Game 5 on May 7.  In tonight’s game, the New York Rangers, who hold a 2-1
lead in their series, travel to Washington to meet the Capitals
in Game 4.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in  Washington  at 
